        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName> <date>Dec. 15. 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">I send you enclosed<lb/> Draft on <persName>Mess. M. Cauffman &#38; Co</persName>&#44; <placeName>Phila.</placeName> Drawn by<lb/> <persName>Roggenburger &#38; Co</persName>&#44; for &#36;24.00&#44; which I have collected for<lb/> the Occident&#44; as per enclosed statement&#59; &#38; enclose you also<lb/> a fresh subscription for the O.&#59; had I more Time to<lb/> spare &#38; our Californians would devote more Time in<lb/> reading your intellectual work&#44; I could&#44; no Doubt have<lb/> sent you a larger list of Subscription.</p>
			<p>I have recd your Letter&#44; &#38; am sorry&#44; that I cannot<lb/> comply with your wishes for informing you&#44; how<lb/> Jewish affairs progress&#59; however that much I can<lb/> tell you&#44; that Jewish Families are getting quite Numerous<lb/> in <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>&#44; &#38; of late we had also several Mar&#45;<lb/>&#45;riages taking place. The Jewish Population all over<lb/> <placeName>California</placeName> is very numerous&#44; but our Religion is<lb/> not by any means kept up in generality&#44; as it should be.<lb/> We have two Synagogues here&#44; one Polish &#38; one German&#44;<lb/> which are open every &#8220;<add>Hebrew</add>&#8221;&#44; but are not very well attended&#44;<lb/> &#38; it is only on &#8220;<add>Hebrew</add>&#8221;&#44; that you have the opportunity of<lb/> witnessing the Synagogues crowded&#44; where there is generally<lb/> not Room enough to seat &#189;.</p>
			<p>It saves me some Trouble&#44; <del>when</del> if I collect the Subscriptions</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>immediately&#44; &#38; you will notice several on my a&#47;c who<lb/> have paid in advance. You will also be kind enough<lb/> to send me the a&#47;c what <persName>Roggenburger &#38; Co</persName> in <placeName>California</placeName><lb/> owes you.</p>
			<p>It was told me by several whose subscription<lb/> to the O. I have sent the Last Time&#44; that they have not<lb/> recd the O. You will please therefore&#44; to be exact in<lb/> making a plain Direction&#59; as our Post office arrangement<lb/> is none of the Best.</p>
			<p>Business in general has been very good with us for<lb/> the last 10&#45;12 Mos. &#38; Goods in almost all Branches<lb/> have paid well to import&#59; some articles always<lb/> pay very well in <placeName>California</placeName>&#59; as for Instance<lb/> Flour is worth from &#36;40 to &#36;45&#8212;pr. Barrell&#44;<lb/> which cost at Home no more than &#36;4.50 pr Barrel.<lb/> I could give you more Information about Business<lb/> but I am aware&#44; it is of no Interest to you&#8212;<lb/> as you are no Doubt aware&#44; money making &#38;<lb/> speculating is all the go&#8212;&#38; one&#39;s attentions is almost<lb/> entirely directed to that.</p>
			<p><persName>Mr. &#38; Mrs. Roggenburger</persName> desire their kind Regards<lb/> to you&#59; they have arrived <sic>save</sic>&#59; &#38; live very hand<lb/>&#45;somely &#38; very convenient&#44; &#38; Enjoy themselves&#59; they live<lb/> &#8220;<add>Hebrew</add>&#8221; &#38; I am boarding with them&#44; which gives me the op&#45;<lb/>&#45;portunity of reminding myself&#44; that I am a &#8220;Secr&#8221;<lb/> Hoping&#44; you will soon write to me a large letter &#38;c&#44; &#38; that this<lb/> may find you in good Health</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">I Remain your true friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Cauffman H Meyer</persName></p>

        </body>
    </text>
